            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "In fact, it seems like this is intended : the `Syntax` event is only triggered with `syntax on`, not whith `syntax off`.\r\n\r\nWell, maybe it would make sense to trigger it for `syntax off` too, so that it would be easy for example to disable spellchecking, custom `match` definitions, etc. with a single `syntax off` command.\r\n\r\n*Edit:* one more thing: it appears that `au OptionSet syntax` also is not triggered by `:syntax off`. So I think there's absolutely no way to launch a command when `syntax off` is set.",
